- I thought this would be a prety relating thread to the general EQ population. I even got a couple of /tells in game lately saying that as soon as they saw the thread, they tried to make their better halves/friends read it to understand what was happening. <br>
We all know EQ is time consuming, more so than a hell of a lot of things in life. And like it or not, the Outsider_01 will never understand why or how we devote so much of our life to it. They will see it as 'waisting your life on a computer game', while we'll see it as having fun and doing just another social activity. <br>
<br>
'I think more about my ex girlie than EQ. We're not insane '<br>
<br>
- I hope - no, I think - you're right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  We're not insane. But surely enough to the Outsider_01, we will appear to be at times. 'Won't stop playing a game in order to come round and watch a movie?!? Just Hit Pause (tm)!' <br>
We'll hear it, they'll say it. Unless they ever succom to the ravages and seductive grip of EverQuest, I fear that this will be a general feeling, or friction, between the EverQuest player, and the Outsider_01 forever.<br>
Solution? 'Honey.. why don't you start a little cleric and see what it's like?' 'Oh, ok, but only for an hour...'<br>
